10 Article – Natural Resources
11 4–701.2.
12 (a) There is a commercial blue and flathead catfish [finfish trotline] license.
13 (b) (1) The license authorizes the holder to catch for sale [blue and flathead]
14 IN THE TIDAL WATERS OF THE STATE:
15 (I) BLUE CATFISH USING, AS DEFINED IN DEPARTMENT
16 REGULATIONS:
17 1. A FINFISH TROTLINE; OR
18 2. A GILL NET WITH A MESH SIZE OF NOT MORE THAN 7
19 INCHES; AND
20 (II) FLATHEAD catfish [in the tidal waters of the State] using a
21 finfish trotline, as defined in Department regulations.
22 (2) A licensee shall fish in accordance with Department regulations.
23 (c) A person who wishes to obtain the license shall complete and submit an
24 application for the license to the Department or any person designated by the Department.
25 (d) An applicant for the license does not need to hold a tidal fish license under §
26 4–701 of this subtitle to be eligible for the license.
27 (e) The term of the license is 1 year from September 1 through August 31 the
28 following year.
29 (f) The annual license fee is $15.
30 (g) A licensee may not transfer a license issued under this section.

6 HOUSE BILL 947
1 (h) A licensee shall have a commercial blue and flathead catfish [finfish trotline]
2 license in the licensee’s possession when the licensee fishes under the license.
3 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act is an emergency
4 measure, is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public health or safety, has
5 been passed by a yea and nay vote supported by three–fifths of all the members elected to
6 each of the two Houses of the General Assembly, and shall take effect from the date it is
7 enacted.
